  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Meyer's NT Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jam 5:19-20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". To the exhortation to mutual confession and intercession is annexed “the reference to an important matter—the reclaiming of an erring soul” (Wiesinger). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jam 5:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " forms the supposition; this is expressed in two co-ordinate sentences, of which the first is subordinate in thought to the second: “if any convert one who has erred from the truth.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
